              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>PALADIN SOLO GUIDE</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Paladin</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">6 to 10</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">East Commonlands</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">In the Grasslands</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">6 to 10</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Paladin Solo Guide - East Commonlands
<br><br>
Well, after moving from West Freeport, you'll enter the West Commonlands.  It's got a few of the West Freeport monsters there, as well as many others.
<br><br>
First thing you should do is fight around an area that's safe, probably the first inn is a good location.  Just follow the dirt road and take it when it splits to the left.
<br><br>
There should be a guard around there, and it's a safe area to fight.  Players occasionally come across there, so you can get help from them if you need it.  And what should you 
hunt...
<br><br>
Well, if you're level 5 or 6, you'll probably still get experience from Fire Beetles, and decayed skeletons.  Well, maybe just a bit...  but make sure by this time (level 6)you go to your guild and learn bash.  It's a useful skill, and since you're probably using a 1H Slash weapon still, find yourself a shield and you'll be able to kill things better.  More damage, plus stunning does help...
<br><br>
Orc pawns might be too weak for you at this time, so your best bet would be to start killing Black Bears.  They're not the most common things to kill, but offer up good experience.  Plus if you're lucky, you can loot a High Quality Bear Skin, which sells for about 30pp to other players.  Other things to hunt that appear more commonly are Large Spiders.  Just watch out for their poison, but it shouldn't do too much.. just don't fight them around other spiders, or they will all gang up on you.  Pumas and Lioness are other things that con blue (maybe) around this level, and although they don't offer up a lot of gold selling pelts is about it), you'll get the experience you need.
<br><br>
When you're a bit higher, say 7-10, you can hunt more of the creatures here.  Kodiaks are soloable, just make sure you don't get attacked by other beras while you're at it, and your lay hands might be needed for it as well.  Lions are good targets as well, plus skeletons that wander the desert area are good too.  Rattle snakes can poison you for a bit, so they might pose more of a risk than normal.  Since a poison will drain a lot out of you, be sure to be prepared by either finishing the battle and bandading (you should carry some around), or asking someone for a heal or cure.  Usually a heal, since the poison will probably be over by the time you reach someone.
<br><br>
When you reach level 9, that's a big jump for the paladin.  You get several new spells, but ones you should note are courage (which is a useful low level buff) and Minor Healing (really useful).  Make sure you put points into the special spell casting skills so you can build them up.  You won't need to put any points into conjuration, since you can't build that skill up until you're level 15.  All the spells you need are at a vendor in either The Temple of Marr, or the Hall of Truth.  Not too expensive either, so you don't need to worry about the price.  And still buy bandages.  You should bandage up to half, and let yourself minor heal the rest up.  You can't med until 12, so you gotta take it easy still and don't get into a fight without yourself mostly medded up.
<br><br>
A tactic that is now possible is that since the new patch, there might be a chance you can heal in mid combat without delaying too much of your attack on the enemy, therefore not losing time on damaging him while healing yourself.  Right after an attack, quickly target yourself and cast light healing, then switch back to the target you're currently fighting.  If you're lucky, you'll successfully cast light healing on yourself before being interupted by the enemy, and make it in time to do the next swing.  It depends on your weapon speed, and a 2H weapon would give you more time to attack than a 1H weapon would, so it works better like that.  You might also want to cast a healing spell right after they swing at you, so that you won't be interupted before you finish.  Mind you, they might bash or kick you still, which will disrupt it.  This should be all you need to follow on soloing to level 10 in the East Commonlands.
<br><br>
Hope this helps.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Samuel Hans (Quellious)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>5.8</b> (average of <b>19</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 146><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><div align=